nib.text:
A woman was critically injured during a shooting in Lind-Bohanon Sunday afternoon, officials said.

Police responded to a report of a shooting at 52nd Avenue North and Bryant Avenue North at 1:32 p.m.

Upon arrival, officers located a woman with a gunshot wound.

Medics transported her to an area hospital, where she was listed in "critical but stable condition," [WCCO reported](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2021/11/14/woman-shot-in-north-minneapolis-2/).

No arrests have been made. This investigation is ongoing.
